## [VALIDATION THROUGH TESTING]

### Historical Test Cases

**Test 1: Byzantine Empire Collapse (1453)**
- Module 9: Semantic (Christian Rome) ≠ Material (military defeat)
- Module 10: Plethon = Declining Power strategizing
- Module 11: In Response phase (1438-1453)
- Module 12: Constantinople as contested node
- **Prediction**: Identity must decouple from state or die
- **Actual outcome**: Plethon develops Hellenic identity theory. After collapse, Greeks survive with this new framework.
- **Validation**: SUCCESS ✓

**Test 2: Soviet Collapse (1989)**
- Module 9: Semantic (ideology) ≠ Material (economy) ≠ Institutional (structure weakening)
- Module 10: Gorbachev = Status Quo Defender attempting reform
- Module 11: In Ideological Counter phase (1985-1991)
- Module 12: USSR as contested space among republics
- **Prediction**: When reformation fails, system breaks faster than new one forms
- **Actual outcome**: Soviet Union collapsed in 3 years, but new system (Russian Federation) emerged chaotic
- **Validation**: SUCCESS ✓

**Test 3: Pax Americana Decline (2020-2025)**
- Module 9: Semantic (liberal order) ≠ Material (capacity declining) ≠ Institutional (rules breaking down)
- Module 10: USA = Status Quo Defender, China = Rising Power
- Module 11: In Structural Response phase (2024-2026)
- Module 12: Mediterranean/Middle East as contested zones
- **Prediction**: 12-18 months to major institutional break, 3-5 years to new normality
- **Actual outcome**: Timeline matches. BRICS formation, CIPS operationalization, NATO fractures visible
- **Validation**: IN PROGRESS - On track ✓

